Os Machpelah, the burying-place near Hebron, very many things are said by very many men. The city was called Hebron, that is, a consociation, - perhaps, from the pairs there buried, Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob, and their wives.

Not a few believe Adam was buried there in like manner: some, that he was buried once, and buried again. “ Adam said, (say thoye), After my death, they will come perhaps, and, taking my bones, will worship them; but I will hide my coffin very deep in the earth, ‘in a cave within a cave? It is there- fore called, the cave Machpelah, or the doublcd cave.''
